<HEAD>Current Quotations</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   ``After all, General (Manuel Antonio) Noriega is (a) much
beleaguered, de facto leader of the Panamanian government. He is
certainly not in a comfortable position, nor are the people of
Panama, which is unfortunate.'' _ White House Chief of Staff Howard
Baker on President Reagan's stepped up economic sanctions waged in
an effort to depose the Panamanian strongman.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``In my heart of hearts, I don't believe I'm going to serve time
because I don't believe a prison sentence is justified even if I
were guilty, and I repeat that I am not guilty.'' Lyn Nofziger,
former White House political director, after being sentenced to
three months in prison for an illegal lobbying conviction.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``It's drugs. McKenzie was drugs, and now this one, all drugs.''
_ Dr. Maria New, chairwoman of the Pediatrics Department at New
York-Cornell Medical Center, on circumstances behind the violent
deaths of toddlers Quintin McKenzie and Maya Figueroa at New York's
largest welfare hotel.
</TEXT>
